        "origin": "web-extension",
        "content": "<p> Assyrian geopolitical policy was based on breaking up and dividing the tribes, nations, ethnic, and linguistic groups of peple they conquered. This mixing of peoples made it possible for the Assyrians to make large-scaled resistance to their rule very difficult. By mixing peoples of different origins and language groups, the made coopeation between the peoples difficult, which left the Assyrians as the sole authorities.</p><p> It also led to the mixing of religious beliefs and practices and the development of religious syncretism, as the Bible itself makes clear. </p>",
        "sectionId": "web-extension-book-twenty-seven-jonah-yunus-the-assyrian-empire-its-religion-a-man-twice-born-from-the-womb"
