        "markerKey": "web-extension-book-twenty-seven-jonah-yunus-the-assyrian-empire-its-religion-a-man-twice-born-from-the-womb:web-extension:8",
        "origin": "web-extension",
        "content": "<p> The Maccabees destroyed Samaria and established Jewish domination over them, which lasted until 63 BCE. The Maccabbean leader John Hyrcanus destroyed the temple on Mount Gerizim in 128 BCE. </p>",
